<h3 id="overview"><a href="#admin_module">Overview</a></h3>

<p>The Admin module provides a comprehensive suite of administrative tools for managing the Comserv application. The system is built with a modular architecture, featuring a centralized dashboard and specialized sub-controllers for different administrative functions.</p>

<p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li>Centralized admin dashboard with real-time system status</li>
    <li>Software deployment and management tools</li>
    <li>Database schema management and migration tools</li>
    <li>System monitoring and diagnostics</li>
    <li>Network management and mapping tools</li>
    <li>Theme and visual customization management</li>
    <li>Comprehensive logging and audit trails</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="admin_dashboard"><a href="#admin_module">Admin Dashboard</a></h3>

<p>The admin dashboard (<code>/admin</code>) serves as the central hub for all administrative activities. It provides:</p>

<h4>Real-time System Status</h4>
<ul>
    <li><strong>System Statistics:</strong> User count, content count, disk usage, memory usage, load average, uptime</li>
    <li><strong>Git Repository Status:</strong> Current branch, last commit, commits behind origin, uncommitted changes</li>
    <li><strong>Starman Service Status:</strong> Service health, uptime information, process details</li>
    <li><strong>Database Information:</strong> Database size, table counts, connection status</li>
</ul>

<h4>Software Management Status</h4>
<p>The dashboard prominently displays software management status with:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Git Status Cards:</strong> Visual indicators of repository state</li>
    <li><strong>Service Status Cards:</strong> Real-time Starman service monitoring</li>
    <li><strong>Deployment Recommendations:</strong> Intelligent suggestions based on current system state</li>
    <li><strong>Quick Action Buttons:</strong> One-click access to common deployment tasks</li>
</ul>

<h4>System Notifications</h4>
<p>The dashboard automatically checks for and displays:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Pending user registrations requiring approval</li>
    <li>Low disk space warnings (80% and 90% thresholds)</li>
    <li>Pending comments requiring moderation</li>
    <li>System health alerts and recommendations</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="software_management"><a href="#admin_module">Software Management</a></h3>

<p>The software management system provides comprehensive deployment and update capabilities:</p>

<h4 id="production_deploy"><a href="#software_management">Production Deploy</a></h4>
<p>Full deployment workflow with backup and restart capabilities. This is the recommended method for production updates.</p>

<h4 id="git_pull"><a href="#software_management">Git Pull</a></h4>
<p>The Git Pull feature allows administrators to update the application codebase directly from the web interface.</p>

<p><strong>How it works:</strong></p>
<ol>
    <li>Navigate to Admin Dashboard → Git Pull or use the quick action button</li>
    <li>Review the current repository status and any warnings</li>
    <li>Execute the git pull operation</li>
    <li>View detailed output and results</li>
    <li>Follow up with service restart if needed</li>
</ol>

<p><strong>Features:</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li>Pre-deployment backup creation</li>
    <li>Conflict detection and resolution guidance</li>
    <li>Detailed operation logging</li>
    <li>Integration with CSC admin support</li>
</ul>

<h4 id="restart_starman"><a href="#software_management">Restart Starman Server</a></h4>
<p>Web-safe Starman service restart with credential-based authentication.</p>

<p><strong>How it works:</strong></p>
<ol>
    <li>Navigate to Admin Dashboard → Restart Service</li>
    <li>Review the service status and warnings</li>
    <li>Provide system credentials when prompted</li>
    <li>Confirm the restart operation</li>
    <li>Monitor the restart process and verify service status</li>
</ol>

<p><strong>Security Features:</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li>Requires system user credentials with sudo privileges</li>
    <li>Secure password handling (cleared from memory after use)</li>
    <li>Detailed operation logging</li>
    <li>Service status verification after restart</li>
</ul>

<h4 id="starman_diagnostics"><a href="#software_management">Starman Diagnostics</a></h4>
<p>Comprehensive diagnostic and repair system for Starman service issues.</p>

<p><strong>Features:</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Diagnostic System:</strong> Automated detection of common service issues</li>
    <li><strong>Auto-Repair:</strong> Automated resolution of detected problems</li>
    <li><strong>Service File Management:</strong> Creation and management of systemd service files</li>
    <li><strong>PSGI File Management:</strong> Automated PSGI application file creation</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="database_management"><a href="#admin_module">Database Management</a></h3>

<p>Comprehensive database administration tools:</p>

<h4 id="schema_manager"><a href="#database_management">Schema Manager</a></h4>
<p>Central interface for managing database schemas and table structures.</p>

<h4 id="compare_schema"><a href="#database_management">Compare Schema</a></h4>
<p>Tool for comparing application schema definitions with actual database structure.</p>

<h4 id="migrate_schema"><a href="#database_management">Migrate Schema</a></h4>
<p>Automated schema migration system for applying database changes.</p>

<h4 id="migrate_pages"><a href="#database_management">Migrate Pages</a></h4>
<p>Specialized migration tool for moving content from Forager to Ency database systems.</p>

<h4 id="get_table_information"><a href="#database_management">Get Table Information</a></h4>
<p>Retrieves detailed information about specific database tables, including schema structure and relationships.</p>

<h3 id="system_management"><a href="#admin_module">System Management</a></h3>

<p>System-level administrative tools:</p>

<h4 id="theme_management"><a href="#system_management">Theme Management</a></h4>
<p>Comprehensive theme system with CSS variable management and customization tools.</p>

<h4 id="view_log"><a href="#system_management">View Application Log</a></h4>
<p>Real-time log viewing with filtering, search, and archived log access.</p>

<h4 id="system_info"><a href="#system_management">System Information</a></h4>
<p>Detailed system information display including hardware, software, and configuration details.</p>

<h3 id="network_management"><a href="#admin_module">Network Management</a></h3>

<p>Network administration and monitoring tools:</p>

<h4 id="network_map"><a href="#network_management">Network Map</a></h4>
<p>Visual network topology mapping and device management system.</p>

<h4 id="network_devices"><a href="#network_management">Network Devices</a></h4>
<p>Device inventory and management system with JSON-based storage.</p>

<h4 id="network_diagnostics"><a href="#network_management">Network Diagnostics</a></h4>
<p>Network connectivity testing and diagnostic tools.</p>

<h3 id="admin_controllers"><a href="#admin_module">Admin Controllers</a></h3>

<p>The admin system is built with a modular controller architecture:</p>

<h4>Main Admin Controller</h4>
<p><strong>File:</strong> <code>Comserv::Controller::Admin</code></p>
<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li>Dashboard functionality and system status</li>
    <li>Starman service management and diagnostics</li>
    <li>System statistics and monitoring</li>
    <li>User activity tracking</li>
    <li>System notifications</li>
</ul>

<h4>Git Operations Controller</h4>
<p><strong>File:</strong> <code>Comserv::Controller::Admin::Git</code></p>
<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li>Git repository operations (pull, status, branch management)</li>
    <li>Deployment workflows</li>
    <li>Backup creation and management</li>
    <li>CSC admin integration</li>
</ul>

<h4>Theme Management Controller</h4>
<p><strong>File:</strong> <code>Comserv::Controller::Admin::Theme</code></p>
<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li>CSS variable extraction and management</li>
    <li>Theme customization and deployment</li>
    <li>Style sheet processing</li>
</ul>

<h4>Network Management Controllers</h4>
<p><strong>Files:</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li><code>Comserv::Controller::Admin::NetworkMap</code></li>
    <li><code>Comserv::Controller::Admin::NetworkDevices</code></li>
    <li><code>Comserv::Controller::Admin::NetworkDiagnostics</code></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li>Network topology visualization</li>
    <li>Device inventory management</li>
    <li>Network connectivity testing</li>
    <li>JSON-based data storage with database migration path</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="authentication"><a href="#admin_module">Authentication & Security</a></h3>

<p>The admin system implements comprehensive security measures:</p>

<h4>Centralized Authentication</h4>
<p>All admin controllers use the <code>Comserv::Util::AdminAuth</code> utility for consistent authentication:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Session-based authentication:</strong> Requires valid user session</li>
    <li><strong>Role-based access control:</strong> Requires 'admin' role in user session</li>
    <li><strong>Automatic redirects:</strong> Unauthorized users redirected to login with destination parameter</li>
    <li><strong>Comprehensive logging:</strong> All access attempts logged with user details</li>
</ul>

<h4>Security Features</h4>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Credential Protection:</strong> System passwords cleared from memory after use</li>
    <li><strong>Audit Trails:</strong> Detailed logging of all administrative actions</li>
    <li><strong>Access Control:</strong> Granular permissions for different admin functions</li>
    <li><strong>Session Management:</strong> Secure session handling with timeout protection</li>
</ul>

<h4>Admin Access Methods</h4>
<p>The system provides two main authentication methods:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong><code>check_admin_access($c, $action)</code>:</strong> Returns boolean, allows custom handling</li>
    <li><strong><code>require_admin_access($c, $action)</code>:</strong> Enforces access, handles redirects automatically</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="git_management"><a href="#admin_module">Git Management</a></h3>

<p>The Git management system has been significantly enhanced with production-safe deployment capabilities:</p>

<h4>Admin::Git Controller</h4>
<p><strong>File:</strong> <code>Comserv::Controller::Admin::Git</code> (965+ lines of functionality)</p>
<p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Safe Git Pull:</strong> Production-safe git operations with automatic backup and rollback</li>
    <li><strong>File Protection:</strong> Advanced file protection using File::Copy, File::Path, Archive::Tar</li>
    <li><strong>Branch Management:</strong> Support for multiple branches with safety checks</li>
    <li><strong>Rollback Capability:</strong> Automatic rollback on deployment failures</li>
    <li><strong>Enhanced Debugging:</strong> Multi-source username checking and detailed session validation</li>
</ul>

<h4>Production Safety Features</h4>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Backup Creation:</strong> Automatic backup of critical files before deployment</li>
    <li><strong>Validation Checks:</strong> Pre-deployment validation of code and configuration</li>
    <li><strong>Rollback Mechanism:</strong> Automatic rollback if deployment issues detected</li>
    <li><strong>Status Monitoring:</strong> Real-time monitoring of deployment progress</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="recent_enhancements"><a href="#admin_module">Recent System Enhancements</a></h3>

<p>The admin system has undergone significant enhancements to improve reliability, security, and functionality:</p>

<h4>Authentication System Overhaul</h4>
<p><strong>Centralized AdminAuth Utility:</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Enhanced Session Validation:</strong> Checks multiple username sources (session, user object)</li>
    <li><strong>Fallback Username Handling:</strong> Uses user_id or 'session_user' when username missing but roles exist</li>
    <li><strong>Improved Debugging:</strong> Better logging for authentication failures with detailed session info</li>
    <li><strong>Flexible Session Checking:</strong> Accepts valid sessions even if username location varies</li>
</ul>

<h4>Controller Standardization</h4>
<p>All admin controllers have been updated to use the centralized authentication system:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Admin.pm:</strong> 51 lines changed - AdminAuth integration</li>
    <li><strong>NetworkMap.pm:</strong> 14 lines changed - authentication standardization</li>
    <li><strong>ApiCredentials.pm:</strong> 13 lines changed - auth improvements</li>
    <li><strong>IT.pm:</strong> 16 lines changed - auth integration</li>
    <li><strong>Root.pm:</strong> 18 lines changed - auth updates</li>
    <li><strong>ThemeAdmin.pm:</strong> 28 lines changed - auth standardization</li>
</ul>

<h4>Documentation System Improvements</h4>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Documentation.pm:</strong> 106 lines changed - major functionality updates</li>
    <li><strong>ScanMethods.pm:</strong> 60 lines changed - enhanced scanning capabilities</li>
    <li><strong>Enhanced Documentation Config:</strong> 10 new documentation categories added</li>
</ul>

<h4>New Dependencies</h4>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Term::Size::Any:</strong> Added for terminal size detection functionality</li>
</ul>

<h3>Usage Guidelines</h3>

<h4>Best Practices</h4>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Use Production Deploy</strong> for comprehensive updates with backup</li>
    <li><strong>Monitor system status</strong> regularly through the dashboard</li>
    <li><strong>Review logs</strong> after administrative operations</li>
    <li><strong>Test changes</strong> in development before production deployment</li>
    <li><strong>Keep credentials secure</strong> and use appropriate system accounts</li>
</ul>

<h4>Typical Workflows</h4>

<p><strong>Code Update Workflow:</strong></p>
<ol>
    <li>Check dashboard for current system status</li>
    <li>Use Production Deploy for comprehensive updates</li>
    <li>Monitor deployment progress and logs</li>
    <li>Verify service status after deployment</li>
    <li>Check application functionality</li>
</ol>

<p><strong>Troubleshooting Workflow:</strong></p>
<ol>
    <li>Check dashboard notifications and recommendations</li>
    <li>Use Starman Diagnostics for service issues</li>
    <li>Review application logs for error details</li>
    <li>Apply auto-repair if available</li>
    <li>Manual intervention if required</li>
</ol>

<p>For more detailed information on specific features, please refer to the individual controller documentation and system logs.</p>
